&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speciality Doctor Old Age Psychiatry &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The following post is available within Greater Manchester West Mental Health NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Speciality Doctor – Old Age Psychiatry – Bolton&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Substantive Post- 8 Programmed Activities (0.8 WTE)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a replacement post and is offered on a substantive basis. The post is based at Breightmet Health Centre, Bolton. The successful candidate will work alongside Consultant Psychiatrists and other health professionals in the Old age Community mental health team and Memory Assessment and Treatment team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is ideally situated to support a healthy work / life balance. We are a dynamic and innovative trust providing an excellent environment in which employees can develop and progress in their career. With our Trust Head Quarters just 3 miles to the north of Manchester City Centre our employees can also enjoy all of the benefits of excellent transport links, great restaurants, a vibrant night life, three local major Football Clubs, City Centre shops and the Trafford centre all within easy reach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are encouraged to apply for posts at Greater Manchester Mental Health NHS Trust who have direct experience of mental health, learning disability or drug and alcohol services either as a service user or a carer. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Trust is committed to safeguarding children, young people and vulnerable adults and requires all staff and volunteers to share this commitment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job description is currently being reviewed by The Royal College. Once appointed we will provide the approved job description.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Benjamin ShawEmail addressBenjamin.Shaw@gmmh.nhs.ukTelephone number0161 357 1297Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Raghu Paranthaman 01204 483 031&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: Raghu.Paranthaman@gmmh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
